1
00:00:21,339 --> 00:00:26,050
HELIS: Oh, speaking of sacrifice, I forgot to tell you.

2
00:00:26,739 --> 00:00:32,482
HELIS: After you crashed the Eclipse network, I sent messengers into the east.

3
00:00:32,482 --> 00:00:37,149
To rally the forces there and mount an invasion of the "sacred land".

4
00:00:38,270 --> 00:00:40,670
I ordered every Nora killed.

5
00:00:42,039 --> 00:00:48,740
I was hoping to catch you there, but, alas, it all seems to have been unnecessary.

6
00:00:48,740 --> 00:00:53,133
Why butcher dozens of innocents for no gain? It's a waste of effort.

7
00:00:53,140 --> 00:00:56,634
You're right. I won't even be there to enjoy it.

8
00:00:56,634 --> 00:00:58,990
The Nora cast me out at birth.

9
00:00:58,990 --> 00:01:01,149
You're not hurting me if you hurt them.

10
00:01:01,149 --> 00:01:04,827
Really? Then it makes no difference one way or another.

11
00:01:10,939 --> 00:01:12,049
More Eclipse.

12
00:01:13,040 --> 00:01:14,789
It's a Corrupted Thunderjaw, alright.

13
00:01:14,790 --> 00:01:17,434
The survivors must be holed up in the mountain.

14
00:01:17,434 --> 00:01:19,788
If the tunnel collapses, they'll be buried.

15
00:01:20,379 --> 00:01:22,489
And I'll never reach the hatch.

16
00:01:29,750 --> 00:01:32,290
ECLIPSE: That's right, bring down the mountain!

17
00:01:41,430 --> 00:01:44,300
SONA: Braves! To Aloy's side, now!

18
00:01:45,003 --> 00:01:46,903
VARL: For Aloy!

19
00:01:46,903 --> 00:01:51,411
SONA: For the Goddess!
BRAVES: For All-Mother! Raaa!

20
00:01:52,715 --> 00:01:56,540
ALOY: Varl, and Sona. They're still alive.

21
00:02:07,569 --> 00:02:10,843
BRAVE: Faithless and forsaken, you will die!

22
00:02:22,534 --> 00:02:25,734
BRAVE: The corruption will not take hold!

23
00:02:37,699 --> 00:02:40,289
BRAVE: Back to the tainted earth, demon!

24
00:02:52,696 --> 00:02:54,700
BRAVE: May the Goddess remember!

25
00:03:07,688 --> 00:03:10,931
BRAVE: Faithless and forsaken, you will die!

26
00:03:22,840 --> 00:03:24,357
SONA: Destroy it!

27
00:03:37,727 --> 00:03:40,000
BRAVE: Back to the tainted earth, demon!

28
00:03:52,708 --> 00:03:55,775
BRAVE: The corruption will not take hold!

29
00:04:08,098 --> 00:04:10,000
SONA: Strike it down!

30
00:04:11,226 --> 00:04:12,953
ALOY: Gotta switch weapons.

31
00:04:22,661 --> 00:04:24,661
BRAVE: May the Goddess remember!

32
00:04:38,700 --> 00:04:40,700
BRAVE: May the Goddess remember!

33
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:56,779
SONA: Bring down the demon!

34
00:05:03,010 --> 00:05:05,010
ALOY: FINISH THEM!

35
00:05:23,040 --> 00:05:24,343
BRAVE: We did it!

36
00:05:24,343 --> 00:05:27,497
[cheering]
VARL: Aloy did it, we only helped.

37
00:05:27,497 --> 00:05:29,184
[cheering]
BRAVE: I thought we would die.

38
00:06:08,399 --> 00:06:12,139
VARL: Aloy, your deeds re-enact the old stories.

39
00:06:12,139 --> 00:06:15,250
VARL: Another metal devil struck down upon the slopes.

40
00:06:15,290 --> 00:06:19,269
VARL: If you hadn't returned, the tribe would have been lost.

41
00:06:19,610 --> 00:06:21,850
VARL: You saved the tribe.

42
00:06:22,199 --> 00:06:25,003
Did what no Brave or War-Chief could do.

43
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,300
I'm glad to see you're alright Varl.

44
00:06:28,350 --> 00:06:30,399
You are alright?

45
00:06:30,410 --> 00:06:34,120
Bruises pale, bones heal.

46
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:37,062
Don't give me a hunting song, Varl. Are you okay?

47
00:06:37,310 --> 00:06:41,140
My body aches but it's nothing that will keep me from fighting.

48
00:06:41,434 --> 00:06:46,067
So much death; is the killing over?

49
00:06:46,067 --> 00:06:51,839
For now, but this was just one battle, Varl. There are more to come.

50
00:06:51,839 --> 00:06:52,850
I see.

51
00:06:53,819 --> 00:06:58,765
So long as we have you to fight with us, I suppose we'll make do.

52
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:01,250
How many survived the attack?

53
00:07:01,310 --> 00:07:05,430
Nearly all the Matriarchs and many families, Goddess be praised.

54
00:07:05,430 --> 00:07:09,250
But Braves? Just a few, and most of them are wounded.

55
00:07:09,740 --> 00:07:13,990
Never before has an enemy stabbed the heart of our people like this.

56
00:07:14,139 --> 00:07:19,069
Even the Carja, in all their Red Raids, never broke through to the Embrace.

57
00:07:19,209 --> 00:07:23,449
Well, this enemy may have broken through, but they never got back out.

58
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:25,239
We made sure of that.

59
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:26,790
They struck from the east.

60
00:07:26,939 --> 00:07:29,209
Our sentinels saw the killers coming.

61
00:07:29,529 --> 00:07:34,949
Said that beside them marched Deathbringers
and Corruptors and other machines driven mad.

62
00:07:35,639 --> 00:07:39,019
We took ground, met them with clouds of arrows.

63
00:07:39,139 --> 00:07:42,050
Some fell, but they kept coming.

64
00:07:42,439 --> 00:07:47,250
Finally, we withdrew to the gates of the Embrace to make our stand.

65
00:07:47,490 --> 00:07:49,149
But they were too much for us.

66
00:07:49,399 --> 00:07:53,100
Those who survived fell back to the mountain.

67
00:07:53,639 --> 00:07:56,350
By law, only Matriarchs are allowed inside.

68
00:07:56,439 --> 00:08:00,609
It was Teersa who broke the taboo, ordered the tribe into the mountain for safety.

69
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:03,332
Lansra, well, she didn't agree.

70
00:08:03,810 --> 00:08:06,867
But I don't think anyone heard her over all the screams and shouting.

71
00:08:06,867 --> 00:08:09,452
Teersa's decision saved lives.

72
00:08:09,452 --> 00:08:14,519
Good for her, common sense isn't always so common around here.

73
00:08:14,519 --> 00:08:16,649
The Matriarchs will be eager to see you.

74
00:08:16,839 --> 00:08:19,834
I'm sure, but I didn't come here for them.

75
00:08:19,889 --> 00:08:22,149
Then what for?

76
00:08:22,290 --> 00:08:23,379
You will see.

77
00:09:01,440 --> 00:09:06,957
BRAVE: My sons. Oh, Goddess, my poor boys.

78
00:09:21,902 --> 00:09:26,284
[coughing]

79
00:09:27,740 --> 00:09:30,663
NORA: How did she know? How is she here?

80
00:09:40,039 --> 00:09:41,250
RESH: You.

81
00:09:43,039 --> 00:09:46,534
Hello, Resh. Still guarding the latrine?

82
00:09:46,534 --> 00:09:48,300
[growls]

83
00:09:51,389 --> 00:09:52,350
ALOY: Teb?!

84
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:59,113
TEB: Aloy! Oh, you've returned!

85
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:02,689
Have you travelled far as a Seeker?

86
00:10:03,039 --> 00:10:05,600
You wouldn't believe the things I've seen, Teb.

87
00:10:05,600 --> 00:10:08,649
I'm glad to see you.

88
00:10:08,919 --> 00:10:12,090
Your injuries, are they serious?

89
00:10:13,169 --> 00:10:14,750
A gash or two.

90
00:10:15,771 --> 00:10:19,240
Nothing I couldn't sew back together with a needle and thread.

91
00:10:20,440 --> 00:10:23,950
Guess being a Stitcher came in handy in combat after all, huh?

92
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,679
[laughs] Yes, I suppose it did.

93
00:10:30,450 --> 00:10:35,350
TEB: You should speak to the High Matriarchs, they're waiting.

94
00:10:49,029 --> 00:10:52,760
YAN: Aloy, I don't know how you survived out there.

95
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:55,806
YAN: Not even Nakoa could have done that.

96
00:10:55,806 --> 00:11:01,759
YAN: Things were easier for a time, once I knew Nakoa was safe.

97
00:11:02,409 --> 00:11:03,850
YAN: But then this happened.

98
00:11:05,240 --> 00:11:09,436
YAN: The goddess must be angry with us, Aloy, for our sins.

99
00:11:13,500 --> 00:11:15,250
ARANA: Aloy, remember us?

100
00:11:17,059 --> 00:11:19,149
I brought Mother's spear with us.

101
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,739
Everything else we had to leave behind.

102
00:11:21,740 --> 00:11:25,100
Glad to see you have it, I know what it means to you.

103
00:11:25,169 --> 00:11:28,100
I hope the enhancement to your spear has proved useful.

104
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,867
Oh, yes. Many times over.

105
00:11:36,429 --> 00:11:39,510
OLARA: Aloy, you've returned.

106
00:11:40,029 --> 00:11:45,129
OLARA: I brought Brom here when the invaders attacked, we barely made it.

107
00:11:45,129 --> 00:11:51,693
OLARA: Teersa declared all Nora
welcome to take shelter in the Sacred Mountain, even outcasts.

108
00:11:52,162 --> 00:11:57,972
OLARA: Brom has been having some difficulty,
but he'll do better now that the explosions have stopped.

109
00:12:05,649 --> 00:12:08,490
TEERSA: Aloy, you've come back.

110
00:12:08,490 --> 00:12:10,559
JEZZA: The Seeker has returned.

111
00:12:11,399 --> 00:12:17,303
NORA: All-Mother, bless this day
and guide me that we would live on in your memory.

112
00:12:18,340 --> 00:12:22,444
JUN: The outcast girl. You taught me a lesson.

113
00:12:23,480 --> 00:12:27,950
JUN: I've remembered what you said many times, I think I'm better for it.

114
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,894
JUN: I was lucky to make it here alive.

115
00:12:31,330 --> 00:12:33,649
JUN: The invasion was terrifying to behold.

116
00:12:34,509 --> 00:12:36,820
JUN: I brought extra stores of Dreamwillow.

117
00:12:39,747 --> 00:12:41,429
JUN: May the Goddess watch over you.

118
00:12:41,430 --> 00:12:43,860
NORA: The machines of the faithless slaughtered our people.

119
00:12:43,860 --> 00:12:45,990
FIA: Aloy! I'm glad to see you again.

120
00:12:47,620 --> 00:12:51,247
FIA: The Dreamwillow you recovered
has comforted many who were wounded in the attack.

121
00:12:52,549 --> 00:12:54,049
FIA: May the Goddess protect.

122
00:12:56,039 --> 00:12:58,629
TEERSA: Come, speak to us.

123
00:12:58,629 --> 00:13:02,757
LANSRA: Foolish woman. You welcome a curse.

124
00:13:02,929 --> 00:13:05,599
JEZZA: Come, Seeker, we have much to discuss.

125
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:09,179
LANSRA: Her very presence here is a blasphemy.

126
00:13:12,440 --> 00:13:15,658
TEERSA: So you have finally returned.

127
00:13:15,658 --> 00:13:16,514
LANSRA: Pfft!

128
00:13:16,514 --> 00:13:21,563
She not only returned but fought her way through many enemies to reach us.

129
00:13:21,563 --> 00:13:24,470
Outside, she brought low a Corrupted Thunderjaw.

130
00:13:24,470 --> 00:13:26,079
She lifted the siege.

131
00:13:26,080 --> 00:13:28,339
JEZZA: How was this done?

132
00:13:28,340 --> 00:13:30,862
By the will of All-Mother.

133
00:13:31,940 --> 00:13:35,200
Have you returned to speak with the goddess, Aloy?

134
00:13:35,210 --> 00:13:39,170
Um, yes, I guess you could say that.

135
00:13:39,539 --> 00:13:41,125
I think it'll work this time.

136
00:13:41,125 --> 00:13:45,094
Sisters! Surely we cannot permit this!

137
00:13:45,094 --> 00:13:49,502
Because of her, our tribe teeters upon extinction.

138
00:13:49,502 --> 00:13:53,240
What if she has come to wake her father, the Metal Devil?

139
00:13:53,240 --> 00:13:56,089
She means to finish our destruction!

140
00:13:56,090 --> 00:13:58,249
We must stop her!

141
00:13:58,250 --> 00:14:00,960
LANSRA: She is a curse made flesh.

142
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,798
LANSRA: She will be the end.

143
00:14:02,799 --> 00:14:06,649
ALOY: I fought my way past an army while you cowered in this cave.

144
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:08,750
You really think you can stop me?

145
00:14:09,340 --> 00:14:11,179
It's time to step aside.

146
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,179
I'm not gonna hurt you.

147
00:14:14,009 --> 00:14:20,090
If there's anything I've learned since the Proving,
it's that there are bigger evils in this world than you.

148
00:14:24,240 --> 00:14:26,340
COMPUTER: Hold for Identiscan.

149
00:14:29,740 --> 00:14:32,960
COMPUTER: Error. Alpha Registry corrupted.

150
00:14:35,139 --> 00:14:37,919
COMPUTER: Correction, Alpha Registry restored.

151
00:14:38,811 --> 00:14:42,735
COMPUTER: Genetic identity confirmed. Entry authorised.

152
00:14:42,735 --> 00:14:46,450
COMPUTER: Greetings Doctor Sobeck, you are cleared to proceed.

153
00:15:24,456 --> 00:15:28,018
COMPUTER: Welcome to Eleuthia cradle 9, brood 1.

154
00:15:34,740 --> 00:15:36,624
SYLENS, THROUGH FOCUS: I see you're inside.

155
00:15:36,624 --> 00:15:38,480
ALOY: Figured I might be hearing from you.

156
00:15:38,929 --> 00:15:40,230
SYLENS: Shall we begin?

157
00:15:40,629 --> 00:15:41,990
ALOY: I never stopped.

158
00:17:02,740 --> 00:17:07,119
ALOY: So these are artificial wombs?

159
00:17:07,119 --> 00:17:10,950
SYLENS: The mothers of a new generation, hundreds of years ago.

160
00:17:11,150 --> 00:17:12,259
ALOY: And me.

161
00:17:22,490 --> 00:17:24,067
ALOY: So this was it.

162
00:17:24,067 --> 00:17:26,099
SYLENS: Where you were born.

163
00:17:26,099 --> 00:17:29,380
ALOY: But … but why?

164
00:18:52,630 --> 00:18:54,318
MULTISERVITOR: Another day has passed.

165
00:18:54,319 --> 00:18:56,660
GIRL: You mean the lights got dim.

166
00:18:56,900 --> 00:18:58,828
BOY: I don't want to sleep, Mother.

167
00:18:58,829 --> 00:19:02,549
MULTISERVITOR: I know. But it is time to get some rest.

168
00:19:02,740 --> 00:19:06,401
BOY: No, I'm king today, what I say goes!

169
00:19:06,401 --> 00:19:10,009
GIRL: I want to see the real sun, not lights and pictures.

170
00:19:10,009 --> 00:19:12,320
MULTISERVITOR: You will in time, children.

171
00:19:12,320 --> 00:19:17,963
CHILDREN: In time! In time! In time! In time!

172
00:19:17,963 --> 00:19:21,429
GIRL: [screams]

173
00:20:11,470 --> 00:20:14,450
ALOY: These look like cribs.

174
00:20:14,740 --> 00:20:17,566
SYLENS: The cradles of a Cradle facility.

175
00:20:17,566 --> 00:20:24,598
ALOY: And those things, the–the multiservitors, they took care of them.

176
00:20:25,299 --> 00:20:27,220
SYLENS: There was no-one else.

177
00:21:48,430 --> 00:21:51,759
MALE: "Someday"? That's what you always say. 

178
00:21:51,759 --> 00:21:53,808
LENA: We want it now!

179
00:21:53,809 --> 00:21:55,745
MALE: It's big down there!

180
00:21:55,745 --> 00:21:57,063
LENA: Now, Father!

181
00:21:57,063 --> 00:22:00,259
MULTISERVITOR: Children, that area is not yet available.

182
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,368
MALE: Get him!

183
00:22:01,369 --> 00:22:03,880
MULTISERVITOR: Physical aggression detected.

184
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:08,027
MULTISERVITOR: Physical aggression is not permitted.

185
00:22:08,027 --> 00:22:09,784
LENA: Except yours.

186
00:22:09,784 --> 00:22:11,507
MALE: Damn sentinels.

187
00:22:11,507 --> 00:22:13,325
MULTISERVITOR: Children, may I be of assistance?

188
00:22:13,325 --> 00:22:15,561
MALE: Go away, healer.

189
00:22:15,561 --> 00:22:17,577
MULTISERVITOR: Lena, you have suffered mild bruising.

190
00:22:17,577 --> 00:22:19,248
LENA: Go away!

191
00:22:40,130 --> 00:22:43,970
So this is where they lived?

192
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:48,748
It's a mess, everything's broken or painted on.

193
00:22:49,039 --> 00:22:51,160
How long did they live here?

194
00:23:20,347 --> 00:23:23,073
MULTISERVITOR: Children, let's run and jump and blow off steam!

195
00:23:23,073 --> 00:23:24,639
FEMALE: Leave us alone, Father.

196
00:23:24,640 --> 00:23:27,569
MULTISERVITOR: After what just happened I can't leave you two alone.

197
00:23:27,569 --> 00:23:28,802
MULTISERVITOR: You broke community rules.

198
00:23:28,802 --> 00:23:30,650
MALE: Just let us talk then.

199
00:23:30,839 --> 00:23:32,186
FEMALE: Go away!

200
00:23:32,186 --> 00:23:34,923
MULTISERVITOR: I'm sorry children, but I must provide supervision.

201
00:23:34,923 --> 00:23:36,869
FEMALE: You're not even a person!

202
00:23:36,869 --> 00:23:41,049
MULTISERVITOR: You sound frustrated. Let's run and jump and blow off steam!

203
00:24:21,410 --> 00:24:23,868
MULTISERVITOR: I have no choice but to release you.

204
00:24:23,869 --> 00:24:25,129
FEMALE 1: But why?

205
00:24:25,130 --> 00:24:27,239
MULTISERVITOR: There is no food here anymore.

206
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:29,368
MALE 2: But there's food out there?

207
00:24:29,369 --> 00:24:30,685
MULTISERVITOR: We don't know for sure.

208
00:24:30,685 --> 00:24:32,085
MALE 1: Come on, let's go!

209
00:24:32,085 --> 00:24:33,449
FEMALE 1: I don't know.

210
00:24:33,450 --> 00:24:36,000
MALE 2: Mother, can we come back, if we're cold?

211
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,969
MULTISERVITOR: I'm sorry, but that won't be possible.

212
00:24:38,970 --> 00:24:43,269
MULTISERVITOR: You will have to support yourselves now,
and take care of each other.

213
00:24:43,269 --> 00:24:44,798
FEMALE 2: What will happen to you?

214
00:24:44,799 --> 00:24:49,509
MULTISERVITOR: I will stay here and sleep and remember all of you.

215
00:24:49,509 --> 00:24:51,609
FEMALE 1: What will happen to us?

216
00:24:52,099 --> 00:24:55,349
MULTISERVITOR: You will be brave and you will learn.

217
00:24:57,140 --> 00:25:01,915
ALOY: They were trapped here their whole lives.

218
00:25:01,915 --> 00:25:05,331
SYLENS: In plain view of luxurious space.

219
00:25:05,690 --> 00:25:07,200
ALOY: What-what went wrong?

220
00:25:07,200 --> 00:25:09,796
ALOY: Why couldn't they access the other areas?

221
00:25:09,796 --> 00:25:13,192
SYLENS: Unknown. But you won't have that problem.

222
00:25:35,539 --> 00:25:38,189
MALE CHILD: Blue is the colour of the sky.

223
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:40,644
FEMALE CHILD: White is the colour of clouds.

224
00:25:40,644 --> 00:25:43,389
MALE CHILD: Yellow is the colour of the sun.

225
00:25:43,390 --> 00:25:45,818
FEMALE CHILD: Green is the colour of grass.

226
00:25:45,819 --> 00:25:49,009
MALE CHILD: Flowers can be any colour, take a look.

227
00:25:49,009 --> 00:25:52,368
FEMALE CHILD: Bees are yellow and black and they love flowers.

228
00:25:52,369 --> 00:25:59,595
FEMALE CHILD: Here they come! Bzz, bzz, bzzzzz… [laughter]

229
00:26:14,700 --> 00:26:17,170
ALOY: Looks like they didn't like this door very much.

230
00:26:17,500 --> 00:26:22,147
SYLENS: It wouldn't open for them, of course they hated it.

231
00:26:22,679 --> 00:26:24,656
COMPUTER: Hold for Identiscan.

232
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:29,900
COMPUTER: Genetic identity confirmed. Entry authorised.

233
00:26:29,900 --> 00:26:33,289
COMPUTER: Welcome to the Lyceum, a place of learning.

234
00:26:34,799 --> 00:26:36,783
COMPUTER: Greetings, Dr Sobeck.

235
00:26:39,839 --> 00:26:43,380
ALOY: So what was this place, exactly?

236
00:26:43,589 --> 00:26:48,130
SYLENS: The dream of Apollo, never realised.

237
00:26:48,130 --> 00:26:49,450
ALOY: But why not?

238
00:27:05,710 --> 00:27:07,285
COMPUTER: Welcome students.

239
00:27:07,285 --> 00:27:13,720
COMPUTER: Please pick up a Focus device
and place it on the side of your head, just behind your eye.

240
00:27:13,720 --> 00:27:18,049
SYLENS: I had to dredge the pits of the world looking for Focuses to repair.

241
00:27:18,099 --> 00:27:21,930
SYLENS: And here sat a trove, enreaching no-one.

242
00:27:27,990 --> 00:27:31,686
SAMINA EBADJI: Hello, child, my name is Samina.

243
00:27:31,940 --> 00:27:33,899
SAMINA EBADJI: Today is a big day.

244
00:27:33,900 --> 00:27:35,960
SAMINA EBADJI: Your first day of school.

245
00:27:36,130 --> 00:27:41,590
SAMINA EBADJI: There's so much for you to learn,
so much promise and possibility.

246
00:27:41,590 --> 00:27:46,474
COMPUTER: Alert. Malfunction. Apollo offline.

247
00:27:46,753 --> 00:27:48,683
ALOY: "Apollo offline"?

248
00:27:48,683 --> 00:27:53,543
SYLENS: You were right, Aloy, this is a graveyard.

249
00:27:53,543 --> 00:27:55,940
SYLENS: The charnel house of knowledge.

250
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:59,508
SYLENS: What we might have achieved, had we not been denied it.

251
00:27:59,683 --> 00:28:04,140
ALOY: Maybe there's a way to fix it. But it's not why I came here.

252
00:28:04,140 --> 00:28:05,650
SYLENS: Of course.

253
00:28:05,650 --> 00:28:09,850
SYLENS: What's the whole of human knowledge
next to the origin of one girl?

254
00:28:09,850 --> 00:28:11,849
SYLENS: Continue your search.

255
00:28:12,670 --> 00:28:13,720
ALOY: I will.

256
