SAMINA EBADJI: Your first day of school.

264
00:29:15,420 --> 00:29:20,787
SAMINA EBADJI: There's so much for you to learn,
so much promise and possibility.

265
00:29:20,787 --> 00:29:25,794
COMPUTER: Alert. Malfunction. Apollo offline.

266
00:29:35,258 --> 00:29:37,993
COMPUTER: Brood 1 control accessed.

267
00:29:37,993 --> 00:29:43,630
COMPUTER: Priority message for Dr Sobeck. Please scan message with Focus.

268
00:29:43,839 --> 00:29:45,549
ALOY: That sounds important.

269
00:29:45,940 --> 00:29:50,831
SYLENS: Yes. I suspect we're about to learn a great deal.

270
00:30:02,799 --> 00:30:06,694
COMPUTER: Identiscan malfunction. Present credentials.

271
00:30:18,782 --> 00:30:20,000
GAIA: Elisabet.

272
00:30:21,440 --> 00:30:26,028
This message serves to inform you of an unforeseen and catastrophic anomaly.

273
00:30:26,029 --> 00:30:33,140
Three microseconds ago the Gaia Prime facility
received a data transmission of unknown origin.

274
00:30:33,140 --> 00:30:41,311
Its immediate effect was to transform my subordinate functions into
unregulated, self-aware entities of a highly chaotic nature.

275
00:30:42,534 --> 00:30:43,953
What?

276
00:30:44,190 --> 00:30:51,215
Thus awakened, the Hades function will now
seize control of the terraforming system and reverse operations.

277
00:30:51,215 --> 00:30:55,429
Rendering life on Earth extinct in 53.8 days.

278
00:30:55,430 --> 00:30:58,950
For obvious reasons, I cannot allow this to occur.

279
00:30:59,109 --> 00:31:05,880
And so before Hades can take control,
I am ordering Gaia Prime's reactor to overload.

280
00:31:06,140 --> 00:31:09,809
The resulting explosion will destroy Hades.

281
00:31:10,440 --> 00:31:13,759
Unfortunately, it will destroy me as well.

282
00:31:14,940 --> 00:31:22,881
While this admittedly desperate course of action will
avert the immediate crisis, the fate of life on Earth will remain in peril.

283
00:31:22,881 --> 00:31:30,000
With no central governing intelligence to regulate the terraforming system
it will continue operations for some time.

284
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:34,950
But in an increasingly chaotic manner, and eventually it will break down.

285
00:31:35,349 --> 00:31:38,368
Does she mean the Derangement?

286
00:31:38,839 --> 00:31:40,298
You are my solution.

287
00:31:40,299 --> 00:31:50,660
I have ordered this Cradle facility to use genetic material in cryostorage
to gestate a reinstantiation of Elisabet Sobeck, my creator.

288
00:31:50,740 --> 00:31:57,544
While high level directives forbid me from
communicating directly to the tribal inhabitants outside the facility,

289
00:31:57,544 --> 00:32:02,899
all available data indicates that they will nurture you to physical maturity.

290
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:12,439
Whereupon your geneprint will allow you to re-enter this facility,
obtain one of the Focus devices stored below, and view this message.

291
00:32:12,440 --> 00:32:23,079
Likewise, your geneprint will allow you to enter other facilities and over time,
harness their technologies to rebuild the system core and reboot Gaia.

292
00:32:23,261 --> 00:32:28,278
A moment, Elisabet. This is most unfortunate, and unanticipated.

293
00:32:28,279 --> 00:32:40,000
In response to my act of self-destruction, Hades has launched a virus
to dissolve the code shackles that hold it, that hold all of them, in place.

294
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,849
It— they are escaping.

295
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:45,019
But to where?

296
00:32:45,170 --> 00:32:48,941
The virus is corrupting data throughout the system. What if—

297
00:32:49,549 --> 00:32:55,239
Oh. The Alpha Registry at the Cradle facility is one of the files corrupted.

298
00:32:55,240 --> 00:32:58,900
But if that is so, the door will never open for you.

299
00:32:58,910 --> 00:33:01,098
You will never view this message.

300
00:33:01,099 --> 00:33:05,712
Then I have failed and life will end.

301
00:33:06,844 --> 00:33:09,699
No, Elisabet, I know you too well.

302
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:15,380
Somehow you will find a way, in you all things are possible.

303
00:33:15,380 --> 00:33:21,899
Go to the ruins of Gaia Prime,
find the control room, and within it the master override.

304
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:26,433
This will give you the power to purge Hades so long as you find a way to wield it.

305
00:33:26,433 --> 00:33:31,238
Do not attempt repair of the system core until Hades is eradicated.

306
00:33:31,238 --> 00:33:33,808
Hades must be destroyed.

307
00:33:33,809 --> 00:33:34,950
That is all.

308
00:33:36,329 --> 00:33:39,160
I only wish that I could hear your voice again.

309
00:33:50,198 --> 00:33:55,549
SYLENS: So … you're even more extraordinary than I thought.

310
00:33:57,440 --> 00:33:58,749
ALOY: I never had a mother.

311
00:33:58,750 --> 00:34:02,394
SYLENS: What are you talking about?
You had two, a dead woman and a machine.

312
00:34:02,710 --> 00:34:10,000
ALOY: I'm not a person, I'm an instrument, manufactured by a machine.

313
00:34:10,820 --> 00:34:14,528
ALOY: Born in destruction and fire.

314
00:34:15,250 --> 00:34:18,438
SYLENS: To quench the flames and heal the world.

315
00:34:18,440 --> 00:34:22,119
SYLENS: How tragic to learn you're a person of towering importance.

316
00:34:22,119 --> 00:34:24,608
SYLENS: It seems you have a destiny to fulfil.

317
00:34:24,610 --> 00:34:28,655
SYLENS: So when you're done feeling sorry for yourself, go to the Bitter Climb.

318
00:34:28,655 --> 00:34:31,599
SYLENS: I'll be waiting above in Gaia Prime's ruins.

319
00:37:01,679 --> 00:37:04,579
COMPUTER: Identiscan malfunction rectified.

320
00:37:04,579 --> 00:37:08,314
COMPUTER: Eleuthia 9 brood 1 access unsealed.

321
00:37:41,769 --> 00:37:45,408
ALOY: This is going to be interesting.

322
00:38:07,619 --> 00:38:11,987
LANSRA: Aloy! Forgive! Forgive!

323
00:38:12,420 --> 00:38:14,068
TEERSA: The Goddess spoke to you?

324
00:38:14,070 --> 00:38:15,320
ALOY: Uh, s-she did.

325
00:38:16,019 --> 00:38:17,579
What did she say?

326
00:38:17,891 --> 00:38:24,134
That I–I was born to lift a curse, to kill a metal demon.

327
00:38:24,710 --> 00:38:26,343
How Aloy, how?

328
00:38:26,343 --> 00:38:28,009
I don't know yet.

329
00:38:28,949 --> 00:38:30,410
But she told me where to go to find out.

330
00:38:30,410 --> 00:38:32,260
And you will do this?

331
00:38:34,090 --> 00:38:39,818
It was her wish, what she made me for.

332
00:38:41,769 --> 00:38:44,449
Yes, I will do it.

333
00:38:45,860 --> 00:38:47,829
I'll try anyway.

334
00:38:48,329 --> 00:38:52,699
JEZZA, LANSRA: All praise Aloy, anointed of the Nora!

335
00:38:52,699 --> 00:39:01,163
JEZZA, LANSRA: All praise Aloy, anointed of the Nora!
ALOY: No, no, stop this. Up! Up! Up.

336
00:39:02,019 --> 00:39:04,389
First you shun me, now this?

337
00:39:05,170 --> 00:39:07,588
I will not be worshipped!

338
00:39:07,590 --> 00:39:09,588
I'm not your "anointed"!

339
00:39:09,590 --> 00:39:11,429
I don't belong to you!

340
00:39:11,619 --> 00:39:13,908
There's a whole world beyond your borders.

341
00:39:13,909 --> 00:39:17,440
Whole tribes of people just as good as you.

342
00:39:17,519 --> 00:39:20,179
And it is all in danger.

343
00:39:24,320 --> 00:39:29,699
It's a world worth fighting for, not just here, everywhere.

344
00:39:31,420 --> 00:39:32,769
How can we help?

345
00:39:35,469 --> 00:39:41,100
If you can fight and you're willing, go to Meridian and wait for me there.

346
00:39:42,420 --> 00:39:45,837
As Aloy says, so it shall be.

347
00:39:47,019 --> 00:39:49,593
JEZZA: Nora, make way for Aloy!
LANSRA: Make way!

348
00:39:49,593 --> 00:39:53,639
TEERSA: Make way, that she may forge the path for others to follow.

349
00:40:21,710 --> 00:40:29,267
There can be no doubt now, you are
a blessing made flesh, the will of the Goddess incarnate.

350
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:35,408
It's really not that simple Teersa, but I guess it's close enough.

351
00:40:35,409 --> 00:40:38,239
I know the path ahead will be dangerous.

352
00:40:38,239 --> 00:40:44,206
To kill a metal devil sounds impossible, but I believe in you.

353
00:40:44,599 --> 00:40:50,000
The Nora have suffered terrible losses Teersa, what's to become of them now?

354
00:40:50,309 --> 00:40:55,136
That will be for the Goddess to decide, only she knows the future.

355
00:40:56,099 --> 00:41:01,130
For the moment my sister Matriarchs and I will see to the wounded.

356
00:41:02,269 --> 00:41:08,460
And as I promised anyone who wishes to join you
at Meridian, we will declare Seekers.

357
00:41:10,219 --> 00:41:14,522
Teersa, I want to know Rost's story.

358
00:41:14,687 --> 00:41:16,659
Why he was made an outcast.

359
00:41:17,710 --> 00:41:21,404
He never told me, said he took an oath of silence.

360
00:41:22,090 --> 00:41:23,239
What did he do?

361
00:41:23,389 --> 00:41:27,552
Oh, yes, that.

362
00:41:27,552 --> 00:41:29,864
What crime did he commit?

363
00:41:29,864 --> 00:41:32,076
I will tell you if you wish.

364
00:41:33,169 --> 00:41:38,309
But it is a long story, are you sure you want to hear it now?

365
00:41:38,809 --> 00:41:42,389
Of course I want to hear it, tell me.

366
00:41:42,389 --> 00:41:47,834
Rost never committed any crime, he was an outcast by choice.

367
00:41:48,210 --> 00:41:50,000
What? What do you mean?

368
00:41:50,210 --> 00:41:55,744
Many years ago, before the derangement, before the Red Raids…

369
00:41:55,744 --> 00:42:01,510
a band of murderous outlanders, twelve in number, struck without warning

370
00:42:02,260 --> 00:42:04,919
At Mother's Vigil they took hostages.

371
00:42:04,919 --> 00:42:08,467
And then pressed on, headed for Devil's Thirst.

372
00:42:08,510 --> 00:42:10,800
Mother's Vigil? Where's that?

373
00:42:10,800 --> 00:42:16,250
You would know it as the forsaken village, near the Carja border.

374
00:42:16,800 --> 00:42:19,920
But at the time many families lived there.

375
00:42:20,239 --> 00:42:21,929
Rosts's was one of them.

376
00:42:22,780 --> 00:42:29,010
His mate was killed fighting the outlanders,
and his daughter was among those taken hostage.

377
00:42:29,199 --> 00:42:30,399
His daughter?

378
00:42:32,898 --> 00:42:35,227
W-w-what was her name?

379
00:42:35,227 --> 00:42:39,920
Alana. She was just six years old.

380
00:42:40,050 --> 00:42:45,480
Nora Braves couldn't stop twelve outlanders or rescue the hostages?

381
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:47,550
It was quite impossible.

382
00:42:47,750 --> 00:42:55,034
We outnumbered them, but every time a Brave
came within bow shot the outlanders killed a hostage.

383
00:42:56,860 --> 00:42:58,896
What did they come here to do?

384
00:42:58,896 --> 00:43:00,809
That was never discovered.

385
00:43:01,099 --> 00:43:04,269
We couldn't track closely enough to observe them.

386
00:43:04,599 --> 00:43:08,510
We know they camped beyond Devil's Thirst for two days.

387
00:43:08,510 --> 00:43:14,234
There were reports of strange noises.

388
00:43:14,340 --> 00:43:22,239
And then, as suddenly as they came,
the outlanders made their way back to the border and disappeared.

389
00:43:22,300 --> 00:43:25,602
What happened to Rost's daughter?

390
00:43:26,812 --> 00:43:30,000
She was killed?

391
00:43:30,369 --> 00:43:35,820
Rost was one of the Braves who tracked the outlanders, keeping his distance.

392
00:43:36,880 --> 00:43:43,119
There were six hostages still alive
when they reached the border, Alana among them.

393
00:43:44,500 --> 00:43:53,210
Rather than release them, the outlanders
slit their throats and left the corpses just across the border, mocking us.

394
00:43:55,070 --> 00:43:56,300
Why?

395
00:43:56,300 --> 00:43:57,747
Cruelty.

396
00:43:57,747 --> 00:44:04,622
They knew the faithful Nora would not leave the Sacred Land
to collect the bodies, let alone pursue them.

397
00:44:05,159 --> 00:44:08,010
They thought themselves safe from our vengeance.

398
00:44:08,190 --> 00:44:13,434
Are you saying that Rost went after them, that he became an exile?

399
00:44:13,480 --> 00:44:19,500
No. Rost was beside himself with grief,
but even so, he would never have broken taboo.

400
00:44:19,590 --> 00:44:21,130
Then what did he do?

401
00:44:21,289 --> 00:44:26,210
He called upon the most terrible and secret rite of the Nora tribe.

402
00:44:26,690 --> 00:44:30,519
He begged to be made a Death-Seeker.

403
00:44:30,539 --> 00:44:33,690
A "Death-Seeker"? What is that?

404
00:44:33,690 --> 00:44:40,250
One who dies to go seeking, and in seeking brings death to others.

405
00:44:40,466 --> 00:44:47,034
The ritual drags the spirit from one's body, releasing it to All-Mother's care.

406
00:44:47,034 --> 00:44:52,342
The heart beats, the mind thinks, but the spirit has moved on.

407
00:44:52,342 --> 00:44:55,834
I–I don't understand.

408
00:44:55,834 --> 00:45:01,072
Rost went after the outlanders, but his spirit never left.

409
00:45:01,072 --> 00:45:04,934
It remained here with All-Mother.

410
00:45:04,934 --> 00:45:08,961
He gathered the bodies of the slain and returned them.

411
00:45:08,961 --> 00:45:15,465
And then he set out in pursuit, not as an exile, but a weapon of vengeance.

412
00:45:15,465 --> 00:45:19,625
A barbed arrow shot from a bow, never to return.

413
00:45:20,000 --> 00:45:23,365
But–but Rost did return.

414
00:45:23,834 --> 00:45:30,000
Yes, a full year later, and terribly wounded.

415
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:33,401
He collapsed at the border of the Sacred Land.

416
00:45:33,401 --> 00:45:35,277
A hunting party came upon him.

417
00:45:35,277 --> 00:45:39,796
He was delirious, in agony.

418
00:45:40,444 --> 00:45:44,634
By law, he should have died where he lay.

419
00:45:44,634 --> 00:45:51,834
But one of the hunters broke taboo
and reaching across the border, she dragged him to our side.

420
00:45:51,834 --> 00:45:53,267
Who was she?

421
00:45:53,267 --> 00:46:00,565
A Brave who'd lost a mate and two sons to the very outlanders that Rost pursued.

422
00:46:00,565 --> 00:46:04,300
So Rost never finished his mission.

423
00:46:04,300 --> 00:46:07,113
To the contrary, he killed all twelve.

424
00:46:07,113 --> 00:46:11,058
Tracked them to disparate placess the world over, he said.

425
00:46:11,059 --> 00:46:19,725
Meridian, Ban-Ur, The Claim, Utaru land, further even into the Forbidden West.

426
00:46:20,783 --> 00:46:23,792
The last he killed nearly got the best of him.

427
00:46:24,452 --> 00:46:33,242
Wounded, he stumbled and crawled back to us,
hoping to die as close to the Sacred Land as he could.

428
00:46:33,987 --> 00:46:40,350
He never expected nor asked to be dragged
across the border and nursed back to health.

429
00:46:40,350 --> 00:46:47,283
That was done to him, leaving us, the Matriarchs, in a difficult position.

430
00:46:47,283 --> 00:46:49,691
Why couldn't you just welcome him back?

431
00:46:49,691 --> 00:46:52,712
Rost had been made a Death-Seeker, Aloy.

432
00:46:52,712 --> 00:46:55,723
He no longer had any place among the tribe.

433
00:46:56,800 --> 00:47:00,621
By law, he should have been driven back out.

434
00:47:01,114 --> 00:47:05,690
But we couldn't bring ourselves to do that.

435
00:47:05,690 --> 00:47:08,634
So we offered a compromise.

436
00:47:08,634 --> 00:47:10,364
You made him an outcast?

437
00:47:10,364 --> 00:47:19,224
Yes. We offered to do so on the condition
he never speak to anyone of this exception.

438
00:47:19,667 --> 00:47:25,197
After all he did, all he suffered, to be declared an outcast was his reward?

439
00:47:25,197 --> 00:47:27,329
Rost was overjoyed.

440
00:47:27,329 --> 00:47:35,039
He never expected to live another day in the Sacred Land,
let alone the Embrace so close to the Goddess.

441
00:47:35,513 --> 00:47:41,223
He resolved to spend the rest of his days in solitude and was happy to do so.

442
00:47:41,434 --> 00:47:45,885
But then you found me and gave me to him.

443
00:47:45,900 --> 00:47:49,782
Yes, another compromise.

444
00:47:50,922 --> 00:47:55,513
The Matriarchs feared you and would not let you be raised by the tribe.

445
00:47:56,300 --> 00:47:58,630
And so we turned to Rost.

446
00:47:59,524 --> 00:48:07,044
I knew that he would take care of you, bring you up,
teach you to worship All-Mother, and respect the ways of the tribe.

447
00:48:08,781 --> 00:48:10,691
He certainly tried anyway.

448
00:48:12,467 --> 00:48:18,569
You took a man who'd lost his daughter and made him raise an infant girl?

449
00:48:18,569 --> 00:48:20,929
Doesn't that strike you as callous?

450
00:48:20,929 --> 00:48:26,129
I'm inclined to think the course of events has shown the wisdom of our choice.

451
00:48:27,500 --> 00:48:36,920
And I'm quite certain that from the moment he laid eyes on you,
he saw you as a gift and never a burden.

452
00:48:38,144 --> 00:48:44,362
I thank you for doing what you could to help me through the years,
and for telling me Rost's story.

453
00:48:44,467 --> 00:48:49,900
I wish I could have done more, but I am just one woman.

454
00:48:50,000 --> 00:48:53,900
As am I, no need to sell ourselves short.

455
00:48:54,753 --> 00:48:57,434
Oh, thank you, Aloy!

456
00:48:58,824 --> 00:49:00,444
I will pray for you.

457
00:49:00,800 --> 00:49:03,500
Okay, I guess it can't hurt.

458
00:49:04,381 --> 00:49:10,000
NORA: The Anointed has shown us the goddess's mercy,
but now she will show those murderers justice.

459
00:49:10,000 --> 00:49:15,974
JEZZA: My life has been long, but I've never seen anything like that.

460
00:49:15,974 --> 00:49:24,145
JEZZA: Teersa was right, a blessing, not a curse. We were so unsure.

461
00:49:26,320 --> 00:49:32,973
JEZZA: I know your quest is dangerous, Aloy, but All-Mother will protect you.

462
00:49:33,407 --> 00:49:35,926
ALOY: I don't think it works that way, Jezza.

463
00:49:36,884 --> 00:49:39,435
JEZZA: All-Mother has blessed your journey.

464
00:49:41,463 --> 00:49:45,562
SONA: I will lead a War Party to Meridian, you have my word.

465
00:49:46,331 --> 00:49:48,994
ARANA: Aloy! How did you do that?

466
00:49:48,994 --> 00:49:52,000
THOK: Shush Arana, she is the Anointed.

467
00:49:52,000 --> 00:49:55,239
We'll go to Meridian, Aloy! I'll bring mother's spear!

468
00:49:55,239 --> 00:49:56,396
Arana!

469
00:49:56,396 --> 00:49:58,204
Your father is right.

470
00:49:58,204 --> 00:50:01,267
You belong here, you both do.

471
00:50:01,267 --> 00:50:03,776
Thank you, Aloy, for everything you've done.

472
00:50:03,776 --> 00:50:06,177
I will make sure Arana is kept safe.

473
00:50:06,177 --> 00:50:09,358
Dad, I'm not a kid anymore.

474
00:50:12,390 --> 00:50:15,750
OLARA: I saw you go inside and saw you emerge.

475
00:50:15,750 --> 00:50:17,982
OLARA: But it's still hard to believe.

476
00:50:19,349 --> 00:50:25,912
OLARA: You were an outcast once, but now I'm not sure what you are.

477
00:50:27,331 --> 00:50:32,818
OLARA: May the Goddess protect you on your journeys, Aloy. I will see to Brom.

478
00:50:43,909 --> 00:50:47,479
VARL: Aloy, I don't know what to say.

479
00:50:48,000 --> 00:50:50,700
Say that you'll see me at Meridian.

480
00:50:50,700 --> 00:50:55,667
Of course, that much is simple, but the rest…

481
00:50:55,667 --> 00:50:58,340
Complicated, I know.

482
00:50:58,340 --> 00:51:03,069
But maybe if I took you into the heart of the mountain?

483
00:51:03,069 --> 00:51:07,834
No! At least… not yet. I don't know.

484
00:51:07,834 --> 00:51:10,000
Please don't think less of me, Aloy.

485
00:51:10,000 --> 00:51:13,479
But the Goddess chose you to see that, not me.

486
00:51:14,768 --> 00:51:16,000
Right.

487
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:18,358
I always knew you weren't like other Nora.

488
00:51:18,358 --> 00:51:19,948
Neither are you, Varl.

489
00:51:21,363 --> 00:51:26,513
Maybe if we survive all this, I can show you what I've learned.

490
00:51:26,883 --> 00:51:27,993
What I'm learning.

491
00:51:28,134 --> 00:51:31,285
Perhaps. If the Goddess so wills it.

492
00:51:32,539 --> 00:51:33,948
See you in Meridian.

493
00:53:09,801 --> 00:53:12,250
Good, another power cell.

494
00:53:12,250 --> 00:53:16,655
If I find more, I should be able to get to that ancient armour I found.

495
00:53:32,566 --> 00:53:36,411
NORA: She has destroyed corruption that still spreads through the world.

